11/04/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The interior ministry reported Friday (8 April) that its Zero Alcohol Tolerance campaign produced positive results in the first three months of the year. Tightened measures resulted in the number of traffic incidents falling by 40 per cent, compared to last year. The number of traffic-related deaths and injuries fell by 20 per cent. (FPB, HIC - 08/04/05)
